  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Combatting Trafficking in Persons in Maldives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is designed to support the Government of Maldives, specifically through revitalizing the National Anti-Human Trafficking Steering Committee, established by the 2013 Prevention of Human Trafficking Act to fulfil its mandate in leading a comprehensive response to combat trafficking in persons (TIP) in the Maldives addressing both sexual exploitation and forced labour. In line with the United States TIP Report 2019 recommendations for the Maldives and building on the achievements and strong partnership with the Government and non-government stakeholders to lead anti-trafficking efforts, IOM will facilitate this project with a view to effectively combat TIP through enhanced policy framework and procedures, robust referral and direct assistance services, and improved protection mechanism for victims of trafficking.</narrative>
  </description>
